<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-08-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-08-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="474" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d474">
                            <head><seg type="margin">[158]</seg> *<hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Field</persName>, Acting Attorney-General, to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Smith</persName>, district
                                    attorney.</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-08-21"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 21, 1869</date>.</dateline>
                            <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">A. H. Smith</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">United States Attorney, Philadelphia:</hi></p>
                            <p>John Fallen, esq., says that William Rand will make all desired
                                explanations relating to the steamer Hornet. See Rand; caution him
                                that he need make none unless he desires it, and that they may be
                                used against him. Then take down all he chooses to say, and send
                                here. The Hornet must not be released, except on the order of the
                                head of a Department, and the marshal will put her in the custody of
                                the Navy Department whenever a naval officer is authorized to
                                receive her. Show this to the marshal.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>W. A. FIELD,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting
                                        Attorney-General.</hi></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>